==English==
===Noun===
'''wainscot'''

#[[wood]] [[panel]]s joined together and used as [[trim]] along the [[wall]]s of a room. Particularly panels of [[oak]] wood.
#:* '''1598''': this fellow will but join you together as they join '''wainscot'''; then one of you will prove a shrunk panel, and like green timber, warp, warp. — [[Shakespeare]], ''[http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/As_You_Like_It As You Like It], iii 3''

===Verb===
'''wainscot'''

#to decorate walls with joined wooden panels.

